    "body":  "Problem to solve: Users can manually type inconsistent or ambiguous qualification titles when adding entries. This makes reporting, matching, and compliance tracking error-prone.\n\nStandardize user-entered qualification titles (e.g., “Aseptic Tech”, “Aseptic Procedures”) to match a controlled master list (e.g., “Aseptic Technique”).\n\nExample flow:\n- User types: Clean Room Handling\n- System recommends: Aseptic Technique\n\nImplementation Approach (Phase 1 MVP)\n\n1. Build a Master List (backend or static)\n[\"Aseptic Technique\", \"SOP Documentation\", \"GMP Compliance\", \"Environmental Monitoring\", \"Visual Inspection\", ...]\n\n2. Use a pre-trained sentence embedding model\n(e.g., all-MiniLM-L6-v2 from sentence-transformers)\n\n3. Create a local vector store (e.g., FAISS or in-memory array)\nCompute embeddings for each entry in the master list\n\n*When user types a new title:\n-Embed the input\n-Compute similarity against the master list\n-Recommend the top match(es)\n\n\n\n",
